quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  23,94,"My Lord, then do not place me among the wrongdoing people."
  23,95,"And indeed, We are Able to show you what We have promised them."
  23,96,"Repel, by [means of] what is best, [their] evil. We are most knowing of what they describe."
  25,40,"And they have already come upon the town which was showered with a rain of evil [i.e., stones]. So have they not seen it? But they are not expecting resurrection.{1}",1:[So they do not benefit from lessons of the past.]
  25,41,"And when they see you, [O Muḥammad], they take you not except in ridicule, [saying], "
  25,42,"He almost would have misled us from our gods had we not been steadfast in [worship of] them."
  26,13,"And that my breast will tighten and my tongue will not be fluent, so send for Aaron."
  26,14,"And they have upon me a [claim due to] sin, so I fear that they will kill me."
  26,15,"[Allāh] said, "